  "response": "Creating a job portal website involves several key steps and components:\n\n1. Planning Stage\n- Define target audience\n- Research competitors\n- Create feature list\n- Choose business model\n\n2. Technical Requirements\n- Domain name\n- Web hosting\n- Programming languages (e.g., PHP, Python, JavaScript)\n- Frameworks (Laravel, Django, React)\n- Database (MySQL, PostgreSQL)\n\n3. Essential Features\n- User registration/login\n- Job posting interface\n- Job search functionality\n- Resume upload/management\n- Application tracking\n- Employer dashboard\n- Candidate profiles\n- Search filters\n\n4. Design Considerations\n- Responsive design\n- User-friendly interface\n- Clear navigation\n- Mobile compatibility\n\n5. Development Steps\n- Frontend development\n- Backend development\n- Database design\n- User authentication\n- Search algorithm implementation\n- Payment gateway integration\n\n6. Additional Features\n- Email notifications\n- Skills assessment\n- Video interviews\n- Recommendation systems\n- Analytics\n\n7. Technologies/Tools\n- Backend: Node.js, Ruby on Rails\n- Frontend: React, Vue.js\n- Database: MongoDB\n- Cloud hosting: AWS, Google Cloud\n\n8. Monetization Options\n- Job posting fees\n- Featured listings\n- Premium employer accounts\n- Commission on hires\n\nNeed more specific guidance on any aspect?",
